TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = Compute("sqrt(2)");

BEGIN_TEXT
The sequence \( \lbrace a _ n \rbrace \)
is defined by \( a_1 = 2 \), and
\[
a_{n+1} = \dfrac{1}{2}
\biggl( a_n + \dfrac{2}{a_{n}}
\biggr),
\]
for \( n \geqslant 1 \).
Assuming that \( \lbrace a_n \rbrace \)
converges, find its limit.
$BR$BR
\(\lim \limits _ {n\rightarrow\infty} a_{n}
= \) \{ans_rule() \}.
$BR $BR
Hint: Let \(a = \lim_ \limits {n\rightarrow\infty}
a_ n \).
Then, since 
\( a_{n+1} = \frac{1}{2}
\bigl( a_n + 2 / a_n \bigr) \), 
we have
\( a = \frac12 \bigl( a + 2/a \bigr) \).
Now solve for \( a \).
END_TEXT

ANS($a->cmp);

